The driver, who was gerast with 210 km / h and hot drink between the legs, receives £1,000 fine
A motorist was imposed a fine of £1,000, because he was driven with up to 210 km / h and a hot drink between his legs.
Andrew Howie, 35, from Tiptree, Essex, was stopped in his Mercedes Benz on the A120 in Braintree on May 27.
After it had stopped by the police, they discovered the beverage cup between his legs.
Before the District Court Colchester Howie is known to be guilty of driving without due care and attention.
He received seven points and a six-month driving ban.
Howie was also sentenced for the payment of costs to the tune of £90 and a victim surcharge of £100.
